Quote:  MUD SNAIL (<i>Amphibola crenata</i>). This is about 3/4 of an inch in diameter and is found in thousands high up on most tidal mudflats throughout New Zealand. ... The Maoris of old esteemed this shellfish as a food and called it Titiko.
